# Responsive layouts (no half-ass breakpoints)

UI must be **designed per breakpoint**, not a phone stack stretched until it looks sparse. If a wide viewport could belong to an unfinished mock, the layout failed.

## Hard rejects (fix before shipping)

- **Stretched mobile shell** — same single column, same left-pinned blocks, growing empty space on the right as the viewport widens
- **Orphan empty containers** — full-width cards/boxes whose content is a short left-aligned list or sentence with a dead zone filling the rest
- **Unbounded measure** — body copy running >~65–75ch without a readable `max-w-*` / prose constraint
- **Chrome vs content mismatch** — header/footer edge-to-edge while main content is a narrow island with no shared align/grid rhythm
- **Breakpoint blindness** — only `px-4` + `max-w-*` and no intentional change at `sm` / `md` / `lg` (columns, split intro, CTA placement, density)
- **CTA row as afterthought** — primary/secondary buttons left-dumped with no wrap, stack, or alignment plan across widths

## Do this instead

1. **Compose for desktop, stack for mobile** — at `md+`, use real structure: two-column intro + aside, step grid, linked resource row, split title/actions — not one endless vertical strip
2. **Fill or constrain** — either content uses the width (grid/columns/sidebar) or the surface shrinks to the content; never a wide empty card
3. **Shared horizontal system** — page shell, nav inner, and main share the same max-width + horizontal padding so edges align
4. **Readable type** — titles can span; body and lists stay on a readable measure (`max-w-prose` / `max-w-2xl` / `max-w-3xl` as fits the page type)
5. **Verify three widths** — ~375, ~768, ~1280: each must look intentional, not “scaled empty”

## Guide / long-read pages

Prefer a clear reading column; if you keep a wide shell, put density in a planned second column or resource rail — do not leave gray/white boxes mostly empty.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — mobile stack scaled up; card is mostly void
<div className="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4">
  <Card><ul><li>One link</li><li>Two link</li></ul></Card>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — measure for copy; adjacent density when width allows
<div className="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 md:max-w-5xl">
  <div className="md:grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_14rem] md:gap-8">
    <div className="max-w-prose">…</div>
    <aside>…related links…</aside>
  </div>
</div>
```

## Checklist (any new/changed page or major layout)

- [ ] Desktop is not just mobile with more margin
- [ ] No full-bleed empty regions inside bordered/filled surfaces
- [ ] Body measure stays readable
- [ ] Nav/content horizontal rhythm aligns
- [ ] Spot-checked phone / tablet / desktop
